article.description: — Casey Jones and Mason Wiliams each scored 13 points as Eastern Washington beat Walla Walla 97-46 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Jones, Wiliams score 13 each and Eastern Washington more than doubles up on Walla Walla 97-46
article.linkText: Jones, Wiliams score 13 each and Eastern Washington more than doubles up on Walla Walla 97-46
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Casey Jones and Mason Wiliams each scored 13 points as Eastern Washington beat Walla Walla 97-46 on Wednesday night. Jones was 5 of 6 shooting and 3 of 5 from the free throw line for the Eagles (1-4). Williams was 4 of 7 (3 for 5 from 3-point range). Jake Kyman was 4 of 9 shooting (4 for 7 from 3-point range) to finish with 12 points. Steele Twiford led the Wolves in scoring, finishing with 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
